Hi tatatodd,

  1. A link to the pip package you installed:
    https://www.python.org/ftp/python/3.5.2/python-3.5.2-macosx10.6.pkg
  2. The output from python -c "import tensorflow; print(tensorflow.__version__)".
    https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/mac/cpu/tensorflow-0.10.0-py3-none-any.whl

Also - what do you mean by "everything else" in "...python 2.7 for the Mac, and 3.5 for everything else."
I mean I also have python 2.7 installed (I understand it is needed by OSX for something), but for my own development, I use 3.5.
